HEADWORD: Divisibility
<hw>Di*vis`i*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>divisibilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being
divisible; the property of bodies by which their parts are capable of
separation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Divisibility</qex> . . . is a primary attribute of
matter.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Divisible</ent>⟦br⟧
